body.p:
You execute the swiftlm-scan command directly to view the metrics. Log on to the Swift
      node as the root user. The following example shows a snippet of the output.
        $ sudo swiftlm-scan --pretty
. . .
  {
    "dimensions": {
      "device": "sdc", 
      "hostname": "padawan-ccp-c1-m2-mgmt", 
      "service": "object-storage"
    }, 
    "metric": "swiftlm.swift.drive_audit", 
    "timestamp": 1442248083, 
    "value": 0, 
    "value_meta": {
      "msg": "No errors found on device: sdc"
    }
  }, 
. . .Use
          the --pretty option. This makes the JSON file easier to read.
